  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Mohd. Tahir Hussain versus State of NCT of Delhi pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_1_911_933','2025INSC100'); ><font size='4'> <strong>MOHD. TAHIR HUSSAIN<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF NCT OF DELHI </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 1 S.C.R. 911</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 100</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010002452025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PANKAJ MITHAL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, AHSANUDDIN AMANULLAH<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup></strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether a purpose based interim bail can be granted to contest the election or for canvassing as the petitioner himself is one of the candidates. Headnotes Interim Bail &ndash; To contest election or for canvassing/campaigning &ndash; FIRs against the petitioner and murder of an official of IB &ndash; Sought interim bail to participate and contest Delhi Assembly Elections, 2025 &ndash; Disallowed by the High Court &ndash; Challenge to: Held: [Per Pankaj Mithal, J.] Interim bail is not permissible for contesting elections, much less for campaigning<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 22-01-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> SPECIAL LEAVE PETITION (CRIMINAL) No. 856/2025</font>  <span style='color:#212F3D' > | Direction Issue :</span><font color='green'> Matter to be placed before Hon\u2019ble the Chief Justice of India.</font> <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-seco